<node TEXT="DEVMEM and DEVKMEM" ID="ID_59149561" CREATED="1318525063165" MODIFIED="1318525078825">
<node TEXT="+         The memory driver provides two character devices, mem and kmem, which&#xa;+         provide access to the system&apos;s memory. The mem device is a view of&#xa;+         physical memory, and each byte in the device corresponds to the&#xa;+         matching physical address. The kmem device is the same as mem, but&#xa;+         the addresses correspond to the kernel&apos;s virtual address space rather&#xa;+         than physical memory. These devices are standard parts of a Linux&#xa;+         system and most users should say Y here. You might say N if very&#xa;+         security conscience or memory is tight." ID="ID_1290750040" CREATED="1318525081014" MODIFIED="1318525095955"/>
</node>
</node>
