<node TEXT="commit 6eb5973594a8f89129cef8410fc364accac96a3a&#xa;Author: Stephen Boyd &lt;sboyd@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Tue May 3 13:04:19 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    msm: clock: Fix error path refcounting&#xa;    &#xa;    When a branch clock fails to enable the power rail, we disable&#xa;    the branch and return an error, but we forgot to undo setting the&#xa;    enable flag. Similarly, if the refcounts are off and a user calls&#xa;    clk_disable() twice, the count for a clock will underflow and&#xa;    wrap around to UINT_MAX. In this situation, WARN_ON() and don&apos;t&#xa;    do anything." ID="ID_66273565" CREATED="1318535308025" MODIFIED="1318535309212"/>
