<node TEXT="commit 29635314793f86ad0de7a12d2c0542342c59c8b0&#xa;Author: Jeff Ohlstein &lt;johlstei@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Wed Apr 20 21:19:28 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    msm: watchdog: always schedule petting on cpu 0&#xa;    &#xa;    2.6.38 has concurrency managed workqueues, so work items can run on any&#xa;    core, and not just the core they are scheduled on. So, specify that we&#xa;    want to pet the watchdog on cpu0, since it doesn&apos;t seem to work across&#xa;    cpus." ID="ID_1534228051" CREATED="1318532816082" MODIFIED="1318532817572"/>
