<node TEXT="commit e256aa70d321b2effc1e1107659cfdbba55a0a8e&#xa;Author: Abhijeet Dharmapurikar &lt;adharmap@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Thu Apr 28 15:47:39 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    GIC: mask private interrupts in suspend&#xa;    &#xa;    The suspend function assumes that the private interrupts even if not&#xa;    marked wakeup don&apos;t need to be masked as they will never trigger while&#xa;    suspended.&#xa;    However that assumption is not true certain timer interrupts (ex DGT)&#xa;    wraps up and causes an interrupt. This interrupt will cause a spurious&#xa;    wakeup from suspend.&#xa;    &#xa;    Fix the suspend function such that private interrupts are not treated&#xa;    specially and will be masked if not marked IRQ_WAKEUP." ID="ID_905028551" CREATED="1318533078923" MODIFIED="1318533080040"/>
