<node TEXT="commit 65b1f23b616807831cea9f3aa4cc1c4e7f08ca53&#xa;Author: Matt Wagantall &lt;mattw@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Wed Jun 8 19:06:33 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    msm: clock-8x60: Add measurement support for RPM-managed clocks&#xa;    &#xa;    Add measurement support for RPM-managed bus and memory clocks.&#xa;    These work the same way locally-managed measurable clocks do.&#xa;    &#xa;    smi_clk and smi_a_clk are a bit of an exception, since the test&#xa;    point runs at twice the set rate of the actual clock. To handle&#xa;    this, the measured rate is divided by two (though if the clock&#xa;    is examined with a scope using the test pad, it will still&#xa;    appear to be running at the double-rate).&#xa;    &#xa;    Also, the measurement hardware may not be able to measure the&#xa;    double-rate SMI clocks for some hardware speed-grades. Erronous&#xa;    software measurements are possible in this case, though the&#xa;    clock can still be correctly observed on an oscilloscope." ID="ID_722287352" CREATED="1318541109601" MODIFIED="1318541110389">
