<node TEXT="commit f3bec1244d5e7963a3e8688b01f33e52be08f80e&#xa;Author: Abhijeet Dharmapurikar &lt;adharmap@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Wed Jul 27 13:16:24 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    power: pm8921-charger: warn when battery is low&#xa;    &#xa;    If the battery is very low print a warning in the kernel logs. This will&#xa;    help debugging restart issues because of a low battery." ID="ID_1254544443" CREATED="1318603585706" MODIFIED="1318603587816"/>
<node TEXT="commit 599dd2bc052cbbb9ce9e73d6f01c5024c0036b6f&#xa;Author: Abhijeet Dharmapurikar &lt;adharmap@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Thu Jul 21 19:57:21 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    power: pm8921-bms: fix the pc calculation algorithm&#xa;    &#xa;    The current algorithm compares if an ocv is between two temperature&#xa;    columns of the same row. This is not valid since the data in one&#xa;    temperature column is collected independently of the data in another&#xa;    temperature column.&#xa;    It is incorrect to assume a relation between ocv values for the same&#xa;    percent row for different temeperature columns.&#xa;    &#xa;    Fix it by finding a percent charge for a bounding temperatures and&#xa;    then interpolating these percent charges based on battery temperature." ID="ID_189368088" CREATED="1318603622408" MODIFIED="1318603623358"/>
<node TEXT="commit 142b502a2af89da0a9ddaaebc6205f83ec69e89c&#xa;Author: Pratik Patel &lt;pratikp@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Thu Jul 21 19:13:34 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    power: fix suspend_sys_sync_wait()&#xa;    &#xa;    Since the workqueue code deletes the work before executing it,&#xa;    checking for no work item being currently queued to the workqueue&#xa;    is not sufficient to guarantee that all the works have finished&#xa;    execution.&#xa;    &#xa;    Use a counter to guarantee that all the pending suspend_sys_sync()&#xa;    works have finished execution before returning from&#xa;    suspend_sys_sync_wait()." ID="ID_118540365" CREATED="1318603901972" MODIFIED="1318603902838"/>
<node TEXT="commit 1d6487cdbfa64b1036a17152ba83163944c1eaa0&#xa;Author: Abhijeet Dharmapurikar &lt;adharmap@codeaurora.org&gt;&#xa;Date:   Mon Jul 11 21:17:23 2011 -0700&#xa;&#xa;    power: pm8921-charger: implement CURRENT_NOW property&#xa;    &#xa;    The pm8921 bms driver can provide instantaneous current. Use the&#xa;    current now property of the power_supply class to expose this&#xa;    feature." ID="ID_1039839024" CREATED="1318605328737" MODIFIED="1318605342385">
